Next, we wish to introduce the concept of angular momentum and the
related space rotations.
In order to define the angular momentum operator ,
we assume (as in canonical quantum mechanics, for observables having a 
classical analogue) that its components are in the enveloping algebra 
of  and 
and moreover that they are linear with respect the components of these
operators. We also require that ,  and  commute with the 
Hamiltonian, and that they span a basis of the Lie algebra . 
The operators with the required properties are:
      _j  = -1    _k,l=1 ^3
