Hence , ,  are the generators of the Lie algebra , 
i.e. they generate the  subalgebra of .
Moreover they are integrals of motion: they do not depend on time.
We shall interpret  as the operator describing the angular momentum
of the WQO, and simply refer to it as the angular momentum.
As in the canonical case, we shall also identify the components of
