The main observation needed is that in the inverse transformations
() only two different vectors  appear, each with a coefficient
of which the square modulus is 1/2.
In order to understand the importance of this observation,
consider an example, say .
The expansion of this vector in the  eigenvectors
(for ) reads:
 
p;1,1,0&=& e^it 2  (v_1(0,1,0)-v_1(1,1,0))
